They teach PROPER SCIENTIFIC (had to capitalise so it‚Äôs easier for you to read) research that shows Enhanced Climate Change is caused by human emissions. Between roughly 400,000 years ago and 1800 the co2 ppm (parts per million) in the atmosphere never went above 250. Now we‚Äôre at over 400. I‚Äôm sure you‚Äôre wondering how we can go that far back. Well in a nice research station in Antarctica call Vostok along with others, they drill into the ice. Each layer of ice represents a year. Within each layer of ice are air bubbles. They use these air bubbles to measure the co2 ppm and also the ratio of O-18 atoms to O-16 atoms to determine an average temperature. And we know it‚Äôs reliable because for recent years the data received from the ice cores show the same things as evidence from trees, and diaries, and global weather stations.
